      • setUserID

        public static void setUserID(UpsightContext upsight,
                             java.lang.String id,
                             boolean preserve)
                      throws java.lang.IllegalStateException,
                             java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Starts a new user session for a specified userID.

        userID cannot be the empty string and has a max length of 256 bytes when encoded in UTF-8 You cannot explicitly log into the anonymous user. The user remain "logged in" between app starts. If there is no userID currently set, the user is tracked as an anonymous user. The anonymous user is treated as a regular user with data persisting between sessions. User Attributes are associated with a userID and will change when a different userID is set. Device sessions are independant from user sessions. Starting a new user session does not start a new device session. SWITCHING BETWEEN USERS: Logging into Existing User: Previous user info is saved and the user is "logged out" (including anonymous users). Existing user is "logged in". Existing User -> Anonymous User: Previous user info in saved and user is "logged out". Anonymous user is "logged in". Existing User -> New User: Previous user info in saved and user is "logged out". A new user is created and "logged in" using the default values. Anonymous User -> New User: The 'preserve' parameter determines whether the anonymous user data should be copied into the new user. If 'preserve' is false, the anonymous user is "logged out", a new user is created using default values and "logged in". If 'preserve' is true, the anonymous user data is copied over to to the newly created user, the new user is "logged in", and the anonymous user data is reset to default.

        Parameters:
        upsight - The com.upsight.android.UpsightContext.
        id - The id of the user that should be "logged in".
        preserve - Determines the behaviour when switching from an anonymous user to a new user.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If called while content is being displayed.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - If called with an invalid userID. (Null, empty, a string larger than 256 bytes when encoded with UTF-8, or UpsightUserSessionInfo.ANONYMOUS_USER_ID).

      • setEnhancedPrivacyApplicability

        public static void setEnhancedPrivacyApplicability(UpsightContext upsight,
                                                   java.lang.Boolean level)
        Sets a level of privacy enhancement to be followed by Upsight.

        Setting this value to null will reduce mediation performance.

        Parameters:
        upsight - The com.upsight.android.UpsightContext.
        level - True if enhanced privacy applies to this user. False if it does not. Null to let the Upsight platform decide.
